===Etymology===
Borrowed from {{bor|en|fro|saphir}}, from {{der|en|la|sapphir}}, {{m|la|sappir}}, {{m|la|sapphīrus}},<ref>{{R:L&S|sapphīrus|sapphirus}}</ref> from {{der|en|grc|σάπφειρος||precious stone, gem}},<ref>{{R:LSJ|σάπφειρος}}</ref><ref>{{R:Strong's|G|4552}}</ref> from a Semitic language (compare Hebrew {{m|he|סַפִּיר|tr=sappī́r}}<ref>{{R:Strong's|H|5601}}</ref>), perhaps ultimately from a non-Semitic source such as Sanskrit {{m|sa|शनिप्रिय||dark-colored stone|lit=dear to Saturn}}<ref>{{R:MW|1051/3}}</ref>.

